1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new approach to neural architecture search (NAS) using a graph search space. This is a fundamental topic in machine learning and specifically in deep learning, which falls under the cs.LG category.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): NAS has been widely used in computer vision tasks, such as image classification and object detection. The paper mentions that the proposed approach can model iterative and branching aspects of the architecture design process, which is relevant to computer vision tasks.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): NAS is a subfield of artificial intelligence, and the paper proposes a new approach to NAS using a graph search space, which is relevant to this category.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on neural architecture search, which is a subfield of neural computing. The proposed approach is based on a graph search space, which is relevant to this category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a new approach to NAS, which can be seen as a control problem. The proposed approach allows for modeling iterative and branching aspects of the architecture design process, which can be relevant to control systems.
